<P><H1 align=center>ADD / EDIT MORTGAGE LOAN – DC074</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT>           </P>
<P><H3>Loan account number: </H3>enter the mortgage account 
number in the field. This must be completed to proceed
<P></P>
<P><H3>Mortgage product description: </H3>enter the product 
type in this field ie. whether it is <A href="HELP_TypesOfMortgageProduct.asp#FixedRate">fixed</A>, <A href="HELP_TypesOfMortgageProduct.asp#SVR">variable</A>, <A href="HELP_TypesOfMortgageProduct.asp#CappedRate">capped etc.</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Purpose of loan: </H3>select the purpose of the loan 
from the drop-down list. There are several options, including ‘house purchase’, 
‘<A href="HELP_MortageTerms.asp#FurtherAdvance">further advance – home improvement</A>’, ‘<A href="HELP_MortageTerms.asp#FurtherAdvance">further advance – transfer of equity</A>’ 
etc. This information is required in assessing the suitability of the 
application, and building up a picture of the applicant’s circumstances. 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Original loan amount / outstanding balance: </H3>if the 
loan was on an <A href="HELP_MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#InterestOnlyMortgage">interest only</A> basis, the original loan amount and outstanding 
balance will be the same (unless the loan has been <A href="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#Redemption">redeemed</A>). If it was on a 
<A href="MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#CapitalAndInterestMortgage">capital and interest</A> basis, the outstanding balance will be less than the 
original loan amount
<P></P>
<P><H3>Repayment type: </H3>select ‘<A href="HELP_MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#InterestOnlyMortgage">interest only</A>’, ‘<A href="MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#CapitalAndInterestMortgage">capital 
and interest</A>’ or ‘<A href="HELP_MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#PartAndPartMortgage">part and part</A>’ from the drop-down list
<P></P>
<P><H3>Interest rate: </H3>Input the interest rate being 
charged on the existing mortgage if known, info may be obtained from applicant.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Monthly repayment: </H3>Input the current monthly 
repayment of the existing mortgage.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Start date / original term: </H3>by entering the start 
date and original term, the outstanding term is automatically calculated in the 
field below 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Redemption status: </H3>select the status of the loan 
from the drop-down list. This shows whether the loan is still outstanding, 
whether it has already been <A href="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#Redemption">redeemed</A>, whether it is to be redeemed via the new 
loan or whether it is to be ported
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK:</H3>clicking on ‘OK’ leads back to <A href="HELP_DC073.asp">Mortgage Loan 
Summary (DC073)</A>, where the details entered are summarised.
<P></P>
